This paper deals with modeling the spread of infectious diseases on social networks, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the impact of indirect contacts on disease transmission, which is related to the study of social networks (cs.SOC). The use of simulation and modeling techniques to study disease transmission also falls under the category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). The paper also uses mathematical models to study disease transmission, which falls under the category of mathematical analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the role of network structures in disease transmission, which is related to the study of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
